cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper focuses on learning to grasp objects using a robot, and proposes a method for improving grasp transfer success. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper uses a view-based model of a grasp and evaluates contacts to generate and score grasps, which involves computer vision techniques. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses learning generative grasp models from demonstration and proposes a method for combining and compressing multiple models. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper involves developing an autonomous training method for the robot to learn from self-generated grasps, which falls under the domain of AI. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with controlling a robotic system to perform dexterous grasping, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
